result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both Operating w/ PAC (4th) and OWI (4th). The defendant was found guilty of Operating w/ PAC (4th) and the other charge, OWI (4th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Joseph M. Conley was found guilty of Operating w/ PAC (4th), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(b).
  • Joseph M. Conley was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: 14CF-182 and 15CF-113 - Both Cases Called @ 1:30 PM: Defendant Joseph M. Conley in court with attorney Thomas W. Johnson.   Scott Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Argument as to SEH by DA.  Argument as to SEH by Atty Johnson.  Argues for lesser conditional time being imposed - agrees with other terms of supervision as requested by the State.  Statement by Def:  Yes.  Atty Johnson - states that Def has been released from sentence in Waupaca Co - remaining 30 days had been stayed.  The Court:  14CF-182:  Theft:  S/W - 2 yrs.  Conditions:  AODA and any follow thru as recommended; Ab Sob; the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, Rest TBD w/established payment structure; Costs plus DNA Surcharge - Sample ordered as to Felony BJump - 60 DTP or PP. 15CF-113:  OWI 4 PAC: S/W 2 yr probation concurrent to existing supervision.  Conditions: 75 days WCJ cond'l time with Huber and GT with 15 days TS credit; Rest owed 14CF-182; AODA and Ab Sob, the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; $1883 fine inclusive of costs; 30 mos DL rev/IID effective today; 60 DTP or PP.  Fel BJump:  S/W - 3 yrs probation.  Conditions same as to all 3 counts with additional N/C provisions with victims JE and LH.  Restitution Hrg to immediately commence.  LH sworn in for testimony.  Direct Exam by DA.  14CF-182 Ex 1 marked - entered and received.  Exam by Court as follow up.  Cross Exam by Atty Johnson.  Re Exam by Court as follow up. Continued Cross Exam by Atty Johnson.  Re Exam by Court as follow up.  Defendant sworn in for testimony.  Direct Exam by Atty Johnson. Cross Exam by DA.  Re-Direct by Atty Johnson.  Argument by DA Blader as to Rest Claim.  Argument by Atty Johnson as to Rest Claim.  The Court:  Factually a very difficult analysis by the Court as to Restitution.  Credible account by victim that $1400 was taken and reported to law enforcement.  Preponderance of evidence exists that $1400 was taken by Defendant.
